ed": true, "mention": "miR-200", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.791605532169342, "span": {"begin": 942, "end": 949}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:29126"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "programmed cell death 1 ligand", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9975883364677429, "span": {"begin": 973, "end": 1003}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:29126"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "PD-L1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9986004829406738, "span": {"begin": 1005, "end": 1010}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5133"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "programmed cell death protein", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9975697994232178, "span": {"begin": 1058, "end": 1087}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5133"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "PD-1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9984297752380371, "span": {"begin": 1089, "end": 1093}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD8", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.5177699327468872, "span": {"begin": 1124, "end": 1127}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD8+ cytotoxic T lymphocyte", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7146602272987366, "span": {"begin": 1124, "end": 1151}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:925"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD8+", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9958582520484924, "span": {"begin": 1124, "end": 1128}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CTL", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7549881935119629, "span": {"begin": 1153, "end": 1156}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:925"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD8", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.7743380069732666, "span": {"begin": 1176, "end": 1179}}], "text": "Incidence concordance  Slug/Snai2, a ces-1-related zinc finger transcription factor gene, confers resistance to p53-mediated apoptosis of hematopoietic progenitors by repressing PUMA (also known as BBC3, encoding Bcl-2-binding component 3) (Inukai et al., 1999; Shibue &amp; Weinberg, 2017; W.-S. Wu et al., 2005).  EMT activation induces the expression of multiple members of the ATP-binding cassette (ABC) transporter family, which results in the resistance to doxorubicin (Saxena, Stephens, Pathak, &amp; Rangarajan, 2011; Shibue &amp; Weinberg, 2017)&nbsp;  TGFbeta-1 induced EMT results in the acquisition of cancer stem cell (CSC) like properties (Pirozzi et al., 2011; Shibue &amp; Weinberg, 2017).  Snail-induced EMT induces cancer metastasis and resistance to dendritic cell-mediated immunotherapy (Kudo-Saito, Shirako, Takeuchi, &amp; Kawakami, 2009).  Zinc finger E-box-binding homeobox (ZEB1)-induced EMT results in the relief of miR-200-mediated repression of programmed cell death 1 ligand (PD-L1) expression, a major inhibitory ligand for the programmed cell death protein (PD-1) immune-checkpoint protein on CD8+ cytotoxic T lymphocyte (CTL), subsequently the CD8+ T cell immunosuppression and metastasis (Chen et al., 2014).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:20:49 +0000 2026"}